BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Tombini Speaks at Congress, Vale Earnings

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-05T03:20:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/brazil-daybook-tombini-speaks-at-congress-vale-earnings.html
Central bank President Alexandre
Tombini will speak at a committee of  Brazil ’s Congress in
Brasilia about inflation,  interest rates  and measures taken by
the government to curb inflation.  GOVERNMENT:
*President Dilma Rousseff meets with German President Christian
Wulff at 11 a.m.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega meets five state governors in
Brasilia at 12 p.m.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini speaks at the Congress
at 10 a.m.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Executives of Gerdau SA, Latin America’s largest steelmaker,
discuss first-quarter results in conference calls with
journalists at 10:30 a.m. and with analysts at 12:30 p.m.
*The Agriculture Ministry releases a forecast for Brazil’s
orange crop.
*The Treasury auctions government bonds LTN and NTN-F; results
will be published at 2:30 p.m.  EARNINGS:
*Gerdau (GGBR4 BZ), bef. mkt.
*Vale (VALE5 BZ), aft. mkt.
*Lojas Americanas (LAME4 BZ), aft. mkt.
*B2W (BTOW3 BZ), aft. mkt.  EQUITIES:
*Cielo (CIEL3 BZ) posted first-quarter net income of 424.6
million reais  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 1.1 percent to 63,615.5.
*The real fell 1.9 percent to 1.6182 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
